{
  "texts": [
    "State-space models (SSMs, e.g.",
    "Harvey, 1990; Shumway and Stoffer, 2006; Särkkä, 2013) provide a flexible framework for modelling time-series data.",
    "An SSM typically involves two components: a model describing the temporal evolution of the latent system state and a model linking the state to observations.",
    "When these components involve linear functions of the latent process, the result is a tractable state-space model, often referred to as a dynamic linear model in the discrete-time context (DLM, see e.g.",
    "West and Harrison, 2006; Petris et al., 2009)."
  ]
}